new.name: CVE-2024-32002
new.description: This repository contains a PoC for exploiting CVE-2024-32002, a vulnerability in Git that allows RCE during a git clone operation. By crafting repositories with submodules in a specific way, an attacker can exploit symlink handling on case-insensitive filesystems to write files into the .git/ directory, leading to the execution of malicious hooks.
